section.section:
In making a determination under paragraph (1) of this subsection, the Commissioner shall consider:
past and prospective loss experience within and outside the State;
underwriting practice and judgment to the extent appropriate;
a reasonable margin for underwriting profit and contingencies;
past and prospective expenses, whether countrywide or specially applicable to the State; and
all other relevant factors within and outside the State.

The Commissioner may withdraw approval of a form or premium rate if the Commissioner:
notifies the insurer in writing of the proposed withdrawal;
specifies in the notice the reason for withdrawal;
states that a hearing on the withdrawal will be held not less than 20 days after the date of the notice; and
bases the withdrawal of approval on a ground set forth in subsection (b)(1) of this section.
